message.content: For a point to be on the $x$-axis, $y=0$.  Plugging this into the equation $y-4=4(x-8)$, we have $0-4=4(x-8)$, so $x=\frac{4}{4}+8=2+8=\boxed{10}$.  For a point to be on the $y$-axis, $x=0$.  Plugging this into the equation $y-4=4(x-8)$, we have $y-4=4(0-8)$, so $y=\frac{-32}{4}+4=-8+4=-4$.  The sum of the $x$- and $y$-intercepts is thus $-4+10=\boxed{6}$.+
